===Etymology 2===
From {{etyl|odt|nl}} {{term|sin|sīn|lang=odt}} (originally a reflexive form), from {{proto|gem-pro|sīnaz|lang=nl}}, from {{proto|ine-pro|seino-|lang=nl}}. Cognate with German ''[[sein]]'', Swedish ''[[sin]]''. Ultimately a form of Proto-Indo-European [[Appendix:Proto-Indo-European_*swé|*swe]], related to Russian [[себя]] (sebja), Latin [[suus]], Greek [[ἑός]] (heos), Sanskrit (sva) etc.

